How open is the team to raising the 4096 server/validator cap or increasing the immunity period? Is this a viable idea right now or just something that will be done in the future?

There are 2 things to consider when doing so:
When you raise the 4096 server cap, you essentially raising the bar for miners. A miner needs incentive to outperform a validator, and with raising that bar, you essentially making it harder for miners to reach that cap. It also pushes more competition on the network, making it even harder to earn Tao. Raising is only an option when a single person has enough computing power to essentially create a "51% attack", meaning that they can hoard enough hotkeys in the immunity period to hoard 51% of the hotkeys. A simple counter to this attack would be to increase the cap, but that would also mean it would become much harder for miners to earn Tao compared to validators.

increasing the immunity period poses a similar risk to the 51% attack, but this time with the added bonus that it's much easier for a miner to keep itself on the network, making a validator much more susceptible to that 51% attack...
Note that the total value for incentive is 1, meaning that more UIDs == less incentive for miners == less risk for validators.
validators are ranked in a similar way, but they use percentage of stake. So more overall stake == less incentive for validator == less risk for miners.

it's not like mining other things... it's not a mindless process and will require getting better at certain elements of ML engineering over time to remain in the game... also requires much time, it's not a set and forget situation, but yes if you are willing to spend the time and enjoy learning and figuring things out, you can do it.... use the discord search before asking a question and if there are hick ups there are people here who will help.
